 # cd /opt; mkdir chj; cd chj
 # git clone https://github.com/pflanze/chj-perllib.git perllib
 # git clone https://github.com/pflanze/recordvideo.git
 # apt-get install libyaml-perl libgtk3-perl mplayer mencoder alsa-utils buffer

Note that we need the mplayer package, not the Ubuntu mplayer2
package; the latter is said to be a separate (and possibly outdated)
fork of mplayer and it won't work for recordvideo!

Then create an Ubuntu style shortcut on your Desktop or whatever, or
perhaps:
 
 # ln -s /opt/chj/recordvideo/recordvideo /usr/local/bin

